<h3>Step 4: Create a Compelling Landing Page</h3>
<p>The landing page sells the tool. It explains the problem, demonstrates the tool, and encourages sharing.</p>
<p><strong>Landing page structure:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li><strong>Headline:</strong> Benefit-focused, includes the tool name</li>
<li><strong>Subheadline:</strong> Explain the problem the tool solves</li>
<li><strong>The tool:</strong> Embedded above the fold</li>
<li><strong>How it works:</strong> 3-step process</li>
<li><strong>Example result:</strong> Show what the output looks like</li>
<li><strong>Why use this tool:</strong> Key benefits</li>
<li><strong>Share buttons:</strong> Make sharing effortless</li>
<li><strong>Related tools:</strong> Link to other tools or content</li>
<li><strong>FAQ:</strong> Common questions</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Example landing page:</strong></p>
<p>Headline: "Free Website Speed Grader"
Subheadline: "Check your site speed in seconds. Get actionable recommendations."
Tool: Input field + submit button
How it works:
1. Enter your URL
2. We analyze performance
3. Get your score and recommendations</p>
